name: Regice ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Ice Barrier
attacks.text: Prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Regice Star by your opponent's Pokémon-ex during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Final Blizzard
attacks.text: If your opponent has only 1 Prize card left and Regice Star is the only Pokémon you have in play, this attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Regirock ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Dig Drain
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Regirock Star.

attacks.name: Final Blast
attacks.text: If your opponent has only 1 Prize card left and Regirock Star is the only Pokémon you have in play, this attack's base damage is 100 instead of 30.

name: Registeel ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Barrier Attack
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Registeel Star by attacks is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Final Laser
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like. If your opponent has only 1 Prize card left and Registeel Star is the only Pokémon you have in play, put 6 damage counters instead.

name: Gyarados ★ δ
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Spiral Growth
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, search your discard pile for a basic Energy card and attach it to Gyarados Star.

attacks.name: All-out Blast
attacks.text: Discard cards from the top of your deck until you have 1 card left. This attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each Energy card you discarded in this way.

name: Pikachu ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Spring Back
attacks.text: If your opponent has only 1 Prize card left, this attack does 20 damage plus 50 more damage.

name: Mewtwo ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Energy Absorption
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for an Energy card and attached it to Mewtwo Star.

attacks.name: Psychic Star
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is an Evolved Pokémon, discard all Energy attached to Mewtwo Star and this attack does 50 damage plus 50 more damage.

name: Celebi ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

abilities.name: Time Travel
abilities.text: If Celebi Star would be Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, you may flip a coin. If heads, Celebi Star is not Knocked Out, discard all cards attached to Celebi Star, and put Celebi Star on the bottom of your deck.

attacks.name: Leaf Shade
attacks.text: Count the amount of Energy attached to Celebi Star. Put that many damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Alakazam ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Psychic Select
attacks.text: Put any 1 card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Skill Copy
attacks.text: Discard a Basic Pokémon or Evolution card from your hand. Choose 1 of that card's attacks. Skill Copy copies this attack. This attack does nothing if Alakazam Star doesn't have the Energy necessary to use that attack. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Alakazam Star performs that attack.

name: Flareon ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

abilities.name: Crimson Ray
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Flareon Star from your hand onto your Bench, you may use this power. Each Active Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) is now Burned.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to Flareon Star.

name: Latias ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Healing Light
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon (including Latias Star).

attacks.name: Shooting Star
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Pokémon-ex, discard all Energy cards attached to Latias Star and this attack does 50 damage plus 100 more damage.

name: Latios ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Miraculous Light
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter and all Special Conditions from Latios Star.

attacks.name: Shining Star
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Stage 2 Evolved Pokémon, discard all Energy cards attached to Latios Star and this attack does 50 damage plus 100 more damage.

name: Rayquaza ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Spiral Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Holy Star
attacks.text: Discard all Energy cards attached to Rayquaza Star. This attack does 100 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon-ex. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Jolteon ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

abilities.name: Yellow Ray
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Jolteon Star from your hand onto your Bench, you may put 1 damage counter on each Active Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Jolteon Star during your opponent's next turn.

name: Vaporeon ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

abilities.name: Blue Ray
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Vaporeon Star from your hand onto your Bench, you may remove all Special Conditions and 3 damage counters from each Active Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spring Back

attacks.name: Spring Back
attacks.text: If your opponent has only 1 Prize card left, this attack does 20 damage plus 50 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Burning Turn
attacks.text: Switch Entei Star with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Detonation
attacks.text: If you have less Prize cards left than your opponent, discard the top 10 cards from your deck.

name: Metagross ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Critical Collection
attacks.text: Count the number of Prize cards your opponent has taken. Search your discard pile for up to that many Metal Energy cards and attach them to Metagross Star.

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Raikou ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Lightning Turn
attacks.text: Switch Raikou Star with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Meta Voltage
attacks.text: If you have less Prize cards left than your opponent, this attack does 40 damage to each of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Charizard ★ δ
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Rotating Claws
attacks.text: You may discard an Energy card attached to Charizard Star. If you do, search your discard pile for an Energy card (excluding the one you discarded) and attach it to Charizard Star.

attacks.name: Dark Swirl
attacks.text: Discard all Energy cards attached to Charizard Star and discard the top 3 cards from your opponent's deck.

name: Mew ★ δ
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Mimicry
attacks.text: Choose an attack on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon in play. Mimicry copies that attack. This attack does nothing if Mew Star doesn't have the Energy necessary to use that attack. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Mew Star performs that attack.

attacks.name: Rainbow Wave
attacks.text: Choose 1 basic Energy card attached to Mew Star. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon that is the same type as the basic Energy card that you chose. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Suicune ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Splashing Turn
attacks.text: Switch Suicune Star with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Cross Wind
attacks.text: If you have less Prize cards left than your opponent, discard all Energy cards attached to all of your Pokémon.

rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Ground Slash
attacks.text: Discard a Fighting Energy card attached to Groudon Star.

name: Kyogre ★
rules: You can't have more than 1 Pokémon Star in your deck.

attacks.name: Critical Collection
attacks.text: Count the number of Prize cards your opponent has taken. Search your discard pile for up to that many Water Energy cards and attach them to Kyogre Star.

attacks.name: Sheer Cold
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, each Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
